owing interest in health insurance generated by implementation of the Affordable Care Act (as well as the coming changes poised to be made to it), Achieving Access will also be useful to policymakers in developing countries and officials working on health policy in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAIDS (Disease)xTreatmentxGovernment policyzBrazil. 0aAIDS (Disease)xTreatmentxGovernment policyzSouth Africa. 0aAIDS (Disease)xTreatmentxGovernment policyzThailand. 0aHealth services accessibilityzBrazil. 0aHealth services accessibilityzSouth Africa. 0aHealth services accessibilityzThailand. 0aMedical policyzBrazil. 0aMedical policyzSouth Africa. 0aMedical policyzThailand. 4aConsumer Health & Fitness. 4aMedicine & Medical Issues. 4aSociology & Social Science.  auniversal health coverage, transnational AIDS movement, democratization, health policy, life-saving medicines, industrializing countries.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501714832?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714832423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714832/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles